<!--
VOICING PLAN:
- Key C. Rhythmically complex, many 8th/16th notes in melody preserved faithfully.
- Harp accompaniment uses quarter/half note chords to provide rhythmic stability.
- LH: C C2-G2-C3-E3; F F2-C3-F3-A3; G G2-D3-G3-B3; Am A2-E3-A3-C4.
- RH: 2-note intervals, mostly thirds and sixths.

VOICE LEADING HIGHLIGHTS:
- RH provides counterpoint to the ornamental melody (steady vs. moving)
- Bass stays on strong beats: C-F-Am-C-G-C-G-C
- LH open voicing throughout for foundation

TEXTURE ARC:
- All measures at moderate density. Harp provides steady harmonic foundation
- for the florid medieval-style melody.
-->
